Argentina football legend Diego Armando Maradona has died at the age of 60 years. The former Albiceleste attacking midfielder and manager had successful surgery on a brain blood clot earlier in November. It was then announced he was to be treated for alcohol dependency. One of the greatest players of all time, Maradona was captain when Argentina won the 1986 World Cup, producing a series of sublime individual performances. He played for Barcelona and Napoli during his club career, winning two Serie A titles with the Italian side. His ‘Hand of God’ goal against England remains one of the controversies of the Beautiful Game in the modern era. More to follow….